aly report.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior spans metric computation plus report emission (`detected and flagged in the anomaly report`), so module handoff is part of the failure mode. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no required real OS/network/subprocess; no AI/ML output dependence; no multi-agentic chain. Rejected System/Agentic/Workflow due absence of those dependencies in behavior text.","test_description":"Run analyzer service with fixture latency distributions (baseline window + spike window) through the normal detection pipeline and report builder; assert p99 ratio >3 triggers a spike flag in the generated anomaly report payload.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Malformed JSON log entries are skipped without crashing the pipeline, and the count of skipped entries is reported.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at parser-to-pipeline interaction: bad records must be dropped while pipeline continues and counter is propagated to reporting. This is beyond a single parse function happy path. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: no real OS/network/subprocess required; no AI output; no multi-agentic sequence. Rejected System+ by behavior text focused on pipeline control flow and counting, not external infra.","test_description":"Feed a mixed in-memory stream/batch (valid + malformed JSON) through ingest→parse→process pipeline modules; assert processing completes, valid entries are retained, malformed entries are skipped, and reported skipped-count equals malformed input count.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.13,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The tool handles a burst of 10,000 log entries per second without dropping entries or falling behind.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Real failure boundary is runtime throughput/backpressure under burst load, which depends on real process scheduling, queues, and timing behavior; in-process mocks can hide drops/lag. REAL-INFRA yes (OS/runtime behavior under load). Rejected Agentic/Workflow: behavior has no AI/ML decision steps.","test_description":"Execute the tool end-to-end as a real process with a load generator producing 10,000 entries/sec for a sustained interval; measure ingest vs processed counts and lag over time, asserting zero drops and bounded backlog growth.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
